Sierra Leone Amends Petroleum Act Granting Government Stake

-- B y   S i l a s   G b a n d i a
-- 
2011-07-12T18:14:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/sierra-leone-amends-petroleum-act-granting-government-stake.html
Sierra Leone’s parliament ratified
amendments to the country’s petroleum law, granting the state-
owned Sierra National Petroleum Co. a 10 percent stake in any
oil block.  Sierra Leone currently has seven off-shore oil blocks
managed by companies including  Repsol YPF SA (REP) , Spain’s biggest
oil company, and U.S.-based  Anadarko Petroleum Corp. (APC)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Silas Gbandia at 
 sgbandia@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net . 